1
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:03,840
{\an8}You're supposed to support me,
not dictate how my life should go.

2
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:05,800
{\an8}- Well, it's because you--
- Let's talk later.

3
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:08,199
{\an8}We're here to take him
on a trip, remember?

4
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:11,080
{\an8}WHEEL ALIGNMENT
SUSPENSION CHECK

5
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:13,120
{\an8}Mr. Thee!

6
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:19,720
{\an8}Mr. Thee! Kongkwan!

7
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,560
{\an8}Kongkwan, honey!

8
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:25,280
{\an8}You should know
what you're supposed to do.

9
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:28,120
{\an8}You can't get distracted like this.

10
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,560
{\an8}And about Veluree too.

11
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:31,880
{\an8}You--

12
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:48,640
Dad, please stop! Dad!

13
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:51,440
You have no right to do this!

14
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:53,120
Dad! Dad!

15
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:58,040
You ran off to Thailand again, didn't you?

16
00:02:58,120 --> 00:02:59,840
I already told you,

17
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:01,800
stop doing stupid stuff like this

18
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:04,360
and start focusing
on our business already!

19
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:07,360
I'm an adult now, Dad.

20
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:09,600
Can you stop forcing me already?

21
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,120
An adult, you say?

22
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:13,920
Yet you still can't provide for yourself.

23
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:16,320
Should I provide for you till you die?

24
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:21,200
Keep drawing your stupid art,
and you'll starve to death for sure!

25
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:25,880
You need to get married
and help me run my business.

26
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,960
And stop it with this nonsense!

27
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:36,440
I'll prove it to you
that my passion isn't some nonsense.

28
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:40,640
I'm going to be a successful designer.

29
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:41,560
Just watch!

30
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,720
Hello, Anna?

31
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:59,080
Dump everything on that desk!

32
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:22,040
Sorry, I need to use the restroom.

33
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:22,960
Let's go.

34
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:25,040
I'll be right back.

35
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:33,360
Where are you going?

36
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:35,080
That was totally not okay.

37
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:36,600
He was touching my leg!

38
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:38,600
Yeah, but please stay with me!

39
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:40,800
Please?

40
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:50,440
Come on. Bottoms up.

41
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:55,880
Drink up.

42
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:14,280
- Are you having fun?
- Yes.

43
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:51,680
{\an8}PLOY

44
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:03,600
What's up? Is something wrong?

45
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:06,640
I'm at my condo.

46
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:08,720
Khim,

47
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:11,200
I want to meet you and Mook.

48
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:12,760
<i>Can we meet tomorrow?</i>

49
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:15,840
Of course. I happen to be off tomorrow.

50
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:19,200
<i>I'll hurry and call Mook tomorrow.</i>

51
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:21,880
I miss you.

52
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:25,640
I miss you both too.

53
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:27,800
I'm hanging up now.

54
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:30,440
Let's meet at our usual spot tomorrow.

55
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:58,560
Eat plenty, so you'll stay healthy.

56
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:05,360
Is something wrong, Mook?

57
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:09,600
Well…

58
00:07:14,840 --> 00:07:16,560
Just tell me what's on your mind.

59
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:18,200
Stop hesitating already.

60
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:23,800
It's Mr. Thee.

61
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:27,600
He told me he wanted
to eat your cooking again.

62
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:30,560
My, my, that's it?

63
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:32,560
I thought it'd be something serious.

64
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:34,560
Is he out of the hospital already?

65
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:38,360
He told me he could leave today.

66
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:43,800
Well, let me know when he's coming,
so I can buy some groceries.

67
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:47,560
Nice! I want to play with Thee again.

68
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:55,640
So you're fine with him
coming to our house now?

69
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:57,320
Well, of course!

70
00:07:57,400 --> 00:08:00,480
And ask him if he wants
to eat anything in particular.

71
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:02,560
Okay, Mom.

72
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:11,320
Don't hold back, okay?

73
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:13,280
I've got a whole nother pot of that.

74
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:14,800
I'll be right back, Mom.

75
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:26,680
What's up?

76
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:29,040
Ploy agreed to meet with us.

77
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,040
Really?

78
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:34,039
She said to meet
at our usual spot after work.

79
00:08:34,799 --> 00:08:38,200
Okay. I'll hurry up and finish work,
then I'll be right over.

80
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:40,960
Mook, she's going to be late!

81
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:42,280
Okay, Mom!

82
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:43,559
I'll talk to you later.

83
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:45,160
I've got to drive my kid to school.

84
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:46,240
See you this evening.

85
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:47,400
See you. Bye.

86
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:51,400
Coming!

87
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:01,960
About Mrs. Anna,
I must apologize again, Mr. Thee.

88
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:07,280
It's alright. I understand.

89
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:08,680
It was my mother's orders.

90
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:10,840
By the way,

91
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:13,960
how much does she know about Mook?

92
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:18,160
Just the basic details
and her family situation.

93
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:23,240
So, my mom knows Mook has a daughter.

94
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:24,840
Yes, sir.

95
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:31,160
Where are you going, Mr. Thee?

96
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:32,400
To go see Mook, of course.

97
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:35,320
Don’t we have a meeting
to finalize the campaign today?

98
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:38,360
Yes, we do. I already arranged
for a meeting room.

99
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:46,920
Come on, Mr. Pitak. I miss my girlfriend.

100
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:53,360
For our campaign with The One,

101
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:55,120
our team at A Round Trip Travel

102
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:57,480
has come up with many special campaigns

103
00:09:57,560 --> 00:09:59,360
so that the customers who are couples

104
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:03,000
may come to The One's hotel
for all services concerning weddings.

105
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:05,440
We'll show you our slides
for more details.

106
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:09,920
Our customers may wish
to travel to Singapore,

107
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:12,080
to other countries,
or also here in Thailand.

108
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:14,920
For Thailand, we tried to find
only the good spots

109
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:18,000
<i>that are hidden gems,</i>
<i>but also trending online currently.</i>

110
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:40,720
{\an8}THANK YOU

111
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:53,080
I'll leave you in charge
of our production and PR.

112
00:10:54,280 --> 00:10:58,120
As for the promotion, I'll have
my hotel's marketing team handle it.

113
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:00,720
Sure.

114
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:04,880
As for the location for the honeymoon,

115
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:08,200
I was hoping we could use
one of The One's hotels.

116
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:10,360
And where's that?

117
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:12,440
Narin Beach Resort.

118
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,040
Narin Beach…

119
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:17,960
Oh, the one we've been to, right?

120
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:23,720
Great. A beachfront hotel's perfect
for the honeymoon campaign too.

121
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:27,800
But I never knew your group
also owned that hotel.

122
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:33,360
Yes, I'm signing a contract
to partner with them.

123
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:38,560
I've had the chance to meet Mrs. Narin.

124
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:40,440
She seems pretty sweet.

125
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:43,920
Enough about work.

126
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,680
Let's talk about your mom.

127
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:51,680
What did your mom say
about me dining at your house?

128
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,400
She said yes.

129
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:02,040
Let me know what day you'd want to come.

130
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:05,680
How about today? I miss Kongkwan.

131
00:12:06,520 --> 00:12:07,960
Not today.

132
00:12:08,040 --> 00:12:10,200
I've got an important meet-up
with my friends.

133
00:12:10,280 --> 00:12:11,360
How about some other day?

134
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:21,520
I'll introduce you to my friends too.

135
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:26,000
Then sure.

136
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:51,080
Hey, don't worry.

137
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:52,920
I'll talk to Ploy.

138
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:03,440
Why isn't she here yet?

139
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:04,760
I wonder if she's okay.

140
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:09,400
She's supposed to be here an hour ago.

141
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:12,560
Should we call her?

142
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:16,560
I'll call her then. Okay…

143
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:24,400
<i>Sorry, the number you've dialed</i>
<i>is currently unavailable.</i>

144
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:26,000
She turned off her phone.

145
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:34,880
<i>Sorry, the number you've dialed</i>
<i>is currently unavailable.</i>

146
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:36,520
Maybe Top already knows?

147
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:43,560
SCUMBAG

148
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:01,920
<i>Don't bother waiting for her.</i>

149
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:04,280
<i>She already knows</i>
<i>about when we had our fun.</i>

150
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:10,680
Khim.

151
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:13,120
What happened?

152
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:16,480
What happened?

153
00:14:29,520 --> 00:14:32,440
Why? Are you telling on me
to your friends?

154
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:37,080
Listen, if you want to have friends,

155
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:39,680
maybe find better ones.

156
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,600
What are you talking about?

157
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:45,720
I don't understand.

158
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:48,360
You're such an idiot.

159
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,760
That's why Khim
could fool you for so long.

160
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:58,800
Take a look at this.

161
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:01,840
Is this your oh-so-nice friend?

162
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:15,920
How could you do this to me? How?!

163
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:18,520
How could you?!

164
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:20,800
I didn't start it.

165
00:15:21,920 --> 00:15:22,920
And actually,

166
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:27,240
she slept with me
the night before we got married.

167
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:29,560
Did she tell you that?

168
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:35,040
You think you can rely
on a horrible friend like her?

169
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,480
You're dumber than I thought.

170
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:17,880
Ploy must hate me so bad.

171
00:16:19,880 --> 00:16:22,320
I'm sure she'll cut me off.

172
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:25,000
Calm down, okay?

173
00:16:25,720 --> 00:16:28,160
I'll find a way to talk to her.

174
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:32,640
We've been mad at each other,
and we've fought,

175
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:35,360
but we've never stopped being friends.

176
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:40,520
But this time, it's seriously bad.

177
00:16:45,560 --> 00:16:47,920
I should've listened to you all along.

178
00:16:52,640 --> 00:16:55,960
I should've stopped being such a playgirl.

179
00:16:58,080 --> 00:17:01,400
What's past is past. Don't blame yourself.

180
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:05,119
Top is the one to blame.

181
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:09,560
I won't let him ruin your lives

182
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:13,119
or any other woman's life anymore.

183
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:21,480
Thank you for understanding me, Mook.

184
00:17:47,320 --> 00:17:50,280
{\an8}VETERAN POLITICIAN RUNS FOR LOCAL OFFICE
INVITES SON-IN-LAW TO ENTER POLITICS

185
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:53,240
{\an8}MINISTER PANSAK IS PAVING THE WAY
FOR HIS SON-IN-LAW TO ENTER POLITICS

186
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:57,480
- Are you for real?!
- Hot, hot!

187
00:17:58,080 --> 00:17:59,160
Hey!

188
00:17:59,240 --> 00:18:01,480
What got you so shocked?

189
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:04,880
Our boss is entering politics!

190
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:13,160
- Mr. Suetrong.
- Yes?

191
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:16,920
Did you know
about our boss entering politics?

192
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:20,040
May I see it?

193
00:18:22,640 --> 00:18:26,560
"Veteran politician runs for local office,

194
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:30,040
invites son-in-law to enter politics."

195
00:18:30,120 --> 00:18:32,600
Huh? I don't think so.

196
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:35,160
He never wanted to enter politics.

197
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:37,920
I think this was a misunderstanding.

198
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:41,440
But that's what the reporter wrote.

199
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:45,600
"Minister Pansak is paving the way
for his son-in-law to enter politics."

200
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:50,160
If he's really entering politics,

201
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:52,280
then what about our company?

202
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:00,760
You got everything right.

203
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:03,400
Thank you so much.

204
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:10,280
Thank you.

205
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:23,120
Is Mr. Pat really entering politics, Prao?

206
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:28,600
Not yet. But I'm going
to have him do it for real now.

207
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:33,040
He'll never be successful
with his stupid travel agency.

208
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:35,640
He's lucky it's not bankrupt yet.

209
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:40,360
I wonder how he'll avoid it this time.

210
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:43,280
Ploy never showed up today.
We can't get a hold of her either.

211
00:19:43,920 --> 00:19:46,080
Do you know where her condo is?

212
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:48,960
I heard she moved to her husband's condo,

213
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:51,040
but I don't know where it is.

214
00:19:52,040 --> 00:19:53,680
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

215
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:07,600
Yes, Mom?

216
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:11,120
I'm sorry?

217
00:20:11,200 --> 00:20:13,280
Have some roselle juice, Ploy.

218
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:15,600
Thank you, Auntie.

219
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:18,200
I happened to have made some today.

220
00:20:18,280 --> 00:20:21,640
You and Khim used to always ask for it.

221
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:24,640
Try it and let me know
if it's still as good.

222
00:20:24,720 --> 00:20:25,920
Sure.

223
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:36,400
It's as good as ever.

224
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:55,880
Mook told me you got married.

225
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:57,160
How has it been?

226
00:20:57,240 --> 00:20:58,560
Are you having a child soon?

227
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:07,240
Marriage is nothing
like I imagined, Auntie.

228
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:16,000
Calm down, honey.

229
00:21:17,160 --> 00:21:21,320
It's normal that you'd have to adapt
in the beginning after you get married.

230
00:21:22,880 --> 00:21:25,440
Every couple has this problem, Ploy.

231
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:29,840
Try to stay calm and work it out, okay?

232
00:21:30,520 --> 00:21:33,000
Auntie…

233
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:49,360
Ploy!

234
00:22:01,160 --> 00:22:03,200
So you know about everything?

235
00:22:05,320 --> 00:22:06,960
Khim told me everything.

236
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:19,520
Ploy!

237
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:30,600
Khim, how'd you get here?

238
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:34,720
I called her.

239
00:22:36,680 --> 00:22:40,000
I think it's time
we opened up to each other.

240
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:48,400
Ploy…

241
00:22:53,640 --> 00:22:55,200
I'm sorry.

242
00:23:02,320 --> 00:23:05,760
I never knew

243
00:23:05,840 --> 00:23:11,320
being pleasure-seeking
would bring me so much pain.

244
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:16,640
You can be mad at me.

245
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:19,240
You can hate me all you want.

246
00:23:19,320 --> 00:23:20,560
I understand.

247
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:26,520
At first, I was really shocked
at what I saw,

248
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:31,680
but the more I thought about it,

249
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:36,560
you were probably suffering
as much as I was.

250
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:49,240
I really didn't know

251
00:23:50,120 --> 00:23:52,880
Top was going to marry you.

252
00:23:55,560 --> 00:23:57,400
But when I found out,

253
00:23:58,720 --> 00:24:02,840
I tried to come clean with you
so many times.

254
00:24:06,040 --> 00:24:07,160
But…

255
00:24:10,320 --> 00:24:12,240
Top threatened me.

256
00:24:13,080 --> 00:24:18,640
He said if I told you about it,
he'd leak the video he took of you.

257
00:24:26,480 --> 00:24:28,120
Khim told me

258
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:30,480
that apart from you two,

259
00:24:31,240 --> 00:24:33,800
he also has videos of other women.

260
00:24:35,960 --> 00:24:38,480
A scumbag like him
doesn't belong in our society.

261
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:45,760
If it hadn't happened to me, I'd find it
hard to believe Top's that kind of guy.

262
00:24:47,160 --> 00:24:50,480
In front of my parents and everyone else,

263
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:53,120
he comes off so good-hearted and polite.

264
00:24:55,360 --> 00:24:59,000
There's plenty of people
who are like him in our society.

265
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:02,720
In front of people,
they act like a good person,

266
00:25:03,840 --> 00:25:07,880
but they secretly save their devilish side
for people who can't fight back.

267
00:25:10,440 --> 00:25:12,960
No one dared to fight him back.

268
00:25:13,040 --> 00:25:15,800
That's why he's still out there
doing these horrible things.

269
00:25:21,680 --> 00:25:23,520
So what are you going to do?

270
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:25,560
Maybe you should tell your mom.

271
00:25:27,600 --> 00:25:31,640
If I told Ma, at most,
we'd just get a divorce.

272
00:25:34,360 --> 00:25:35,400
So what's your plan?

273
00:25:39,520 --> 00:25:43,720
We need to stop him together,
so he can't hurt anyone else.

274
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:46,400
I'll tell the police.

275
00:25:50,240 --> 00:25:52,000
Have you seen the news, Mr. Pat?

276
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:53,840
What news?

277
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:06,480
I'm sure Prao's behind it.

278
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:09,440
I thought so too.

279
00:26:14,560 --> 00:26:16,640
PRAO

280
00:26:21,480 --> 00:26:22,880
What is it, Prao?

281
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:30,040
Sure. I wanted to meet you anyway.

282
00:26:31,720 --> 00:26:36,440
Who knew it'd always be so hard
to meet my son-in-law?

283
00:26:37,160 --> 00:26:39,440
Last time, you just up and ran off.

284
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:43,520
I'm sorry, Dad.

285
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:46,600
I'm not used to being around
that many people.

286
00:26:49,200 --> 00:26:51,320
Well, learn to get used to it.

287
00:26:51,400 --> 00:26:54,440
Soon, you'll enter politics
and work with me.

288
00:26:54,520 --> 00:26:56,760
You'll have to meet lots of people.

289
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:03,600
My dad invited you today

290
00:27:04,280 --> 00:27:06,760
because he really wanted you

291
00:27:06,840 --> 00:27:09,160
to officially work with him.

292
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:12,760
There's about to be a local election.

293
00:27:12,840 --> 00:27:14,920
Dad wants you to run.

294
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:19,280
I already told you, Prao,
I don't want to enter politics.

295
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:28,640
I'm really not fit for it, Dad.

296
00:27:28,720 --> 00:27:30,640
You should find someone else.

297
00:27:32,800 --> 00:27:35,160
How long will you keep on struggling
with your agency?

298
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:38,720
I heard you've been in the red
for two years now, haven't you?

299
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:41,800
I'm working on fixing it,

300
00:27:42,560 --> 00:27:44,240
and we've been doing better.

301
00:28:07,960 --> 00:28:10,160
You can cash however much you'd like.

302
00:28:10,840 --> 00:28:12,960
Think of it as a bonus
I'm paying in advance.

303
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:16,360
Then, come work with me officially.

304
00:28:16,440 --> 00:28:19,160
As for your travel agency,
if you want to keep running it,

305
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:20,480
that's fine by me.

306
00:28:20,560 --> 00:28:22,440
But do it as a hobby,

307
00:28:22,520 --> 00:28:25,640
or find someone you trust
to run it for you.

308
00:28:30,560 --> 00:28:33,600
See? Dad just wants what's best for you.

309
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:36,880
Please accept it.

310
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:39,160
Because if you don't,

311
00:28:39,240 --> 00:28:42,320
who knows when you'll finally solve
your company's problems.

312
00:28:44,800 --> 00:28:46,360
I really can't accept it.

313
00:28:47,320 --> 00:28:50,560
Not this check
and not the job in politics.

314
00:28:50,640 --> 00:28:54,480
I can deal with my own problems.

315
00:28:55,080 --> 00:28:56,400
If you'll excuse me.

316
00:28:58,680 --> 00:28:59,680
Pat!

317
00:29:09,760 --> 00:29:11,480
With photos and videos secretly taken,

318
00:29:12,640 --> 00:29:15,960
if only the victim or the plaintiff
appears in them,

319
00:29:16,040 --> 00:29:18,400
they cannot indicate
who the perpetrator is.

320
00:29:18,480 --> 00:29:22,200
But my husband
really took those videos, Officer.

321
00:29:22,960 --> 00:29:25,600
- It's true!
- Then, I can file a report

322
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:28,680
and look for more evidence for this case.

323
00:29:28,760 --> 00:29:31,480
In the meantime, if you two

324
00:29:31,560 --> 00:29:34,160
have definitive proof
that he committed the crime,

325
00:29:34,240 --> 00:29:35,480
please report it right away.

326
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:51,320
What should we do now? If we keep waiting,

327
00:29:51,400 --> 00:29:53,240
Top will surely catch on to us first.

328
00:29:58,360 --> 00:30:00,640
I'm going to find the evidence myself.

329
00:30:01,720 --> 00:30:04,560
I'll make sure
that scumbag won't get away.

330
00:30:07,800 --> 00:30:09,560
You sure have changed a lot, Ploy.

331
00:30:13,560 --> 00:30:15,240
I don't want to run away anymore, Khim.

332
00:30:19,160 --> 00:30:20,600
Me neither.

333
00:30:23,440 --> 00:30:26,600
If I can help in any way,
please let me know.

334
00:30:27,280 --> 00:30:30,000
Let's deal with that scumbag together.

335
00:30:53,640 --> 00:30:54,680
Alright.

336
00:30:56,360 --> 00:30:58,360
Whoa, hey!

337
00:30:58,440 --> 00:30:59,520
We're just having dinner.

338
00:30:59,600 --> 00:31:01,160
You didn't have to buy a gift basket.

339
00:31:01,240 --> 00:31:03,680
Your mom's making me something delicious,

340
00:31:03,760 --> 00:31:06,040
so, of course,
I couldn't come empty-handed.

341
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:08,800
Okay, let's go.

342
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:11,000
What? Why are you handing me that?

343
00:31:11,080 --> 00:31:12,400
Go give it to her yourself.

344
00:31:12,480 --> 00:31:13,600
Please just hold it for me.

345
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:15,320
I have to grab Kongkwan's gift.

346
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:34,920
Let's head inside. My mom's
made lots of delicious food.

347
00:31:37,040 --> 00:31:38,080
This way.

348
00:31:44,720 --> 00:31:46,040
Thank you.

349
00:31:46,120 --> 00:31:47,920
Please save your money next time.

350
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:49,640
I'm just happy to have dinner with you.

351
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:51,080
Okay.

352
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:55,360
- Careful!
- Thee's here!

353
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:57,000
Good evening, Thee.

354
00:31:57,080 --> 00:32:00,000
Good evening. I got you something too.

355
00:32:00,640 --> 00:32:01,480
What is it?

356
00:32:06,120 --> 00:32:08,640
Here it is! A huge box of colored pencils.

357
00:32:09,240 --> 00:32:10,800
Thank you, Thee.

358
00:32:13,080 --> 00:32:15,120
Can we color together sometime?

359
00:32:16,080 --> 00:32:17,360
Of course.

360
00:32:20,120 --> 00:32:22,640
Let's eat before the food gets cold.

361
00:32:23,320 --> 00:32:25,920
- Sure.
- Let's go, Thee.

362
00:32:27,840 --> 00:32:29,360
Go on.

363
00:32:30,280 --> 00:32:31,360
Let's go.

364
00:32:32,720 --> 00:32:33,920
Is it this way?

365
00:33:12,520 --> 00:33:14,360
Here? Okay.

366
00:33:15,520 --> 00:33:17,480
- There.
- Not like that.

367
00:33:17,560 --> 00:33:19,120
- Yeah.
- Let's finish this part first.

368
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:21,920
You can color this part blue.

369
00:33:23,120 --> 00:33:25,000
Can I help you, Mom?

370
00:33:25,920 --> 00:33:28,120
Those two are still playing together?

371
00:33:29,120 --> 00:33:32,400
Yeah. They're stuck together like glue.

372
00:33:33,200 --> 00:33:35,520
Kongkwan seems very happy today.

373
00:33:35,600 --> 00:33:37,440
She must be happy to have a new friend.

374
00:33:45,720 --> 00:33:48,280
Where there's joy, there's also sorrow.

375
00:33:51,280 --> 00:33:53,240
I want you to be prepared.

376
00:33:58,880 --> 00:33:59,920
Yes, Mom.

377
00:34:00,960 --> 00:34:02,800
I'll remember your words.

378
00:34:03,840 --> 00:34:08,159
When the day comes,
I'll be prepared to handle it.

379
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:12,159
Thank you.

380
00:34:19,120 --> 00:34:20,840
The food was so good.

381
00:34:20,920 --> 00:34:23,320
It's been a while
since I got to eat your cooking.

382
00:34:24,600 --> 00:34:26,040
Come again anytime.

383
00:34:26,120 --> 00:34:27,400
You're always welcome here.

384
00:34:27,480 --> 00:34:28,560
Thank you.

385
00:34:39,440 --> 00:34:40,840
Ma'am,

386
00:34:40,920 --> 00:34:43,520
would you and Kongkwan
like to go to the beach with me?

387
00:34:45,560 --> 00:34:49,320
Mook and I are planning to go
and scout the venue for our campaign.

388
00:34:49,400 --> 00:34:51,440
Yay! The beach?

389
00:34:51,520 --> 00:34:52,880
I want to go too.

390
00:34:52,960 --> 00:34:54,560
I want to go to the beach.

391
00:34:55,920 --> 00:34:59,720
Please, let me come with you. Please?

392
00:35:01,080 --> 00:35:02,320
Please join us, ma'am.

393
00:35:08,760 --> 00:35:09,960
I'll take that as a yes.

394
00:35:12,040 --> 00:35:15,240
Then, if you'll excuse me. Goodnight.

395
00:35:15,320 --> 00:35:16,440
Goodnight.

396
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:20,640
Kongkwan, I'll be going now.

397
00:35:20,720 --> 00:35:22,920
Goodnight, Thee.

398
00:35:24,040 --> 00:35:26,400
A promise is a promise, okay?

399
00:35:27,760 --> 00:35:28,880
I promise.

400
00:35:32,840 --> 00:35:35,280
Come here. Sit with me for a minute.

401
00:35:35,360 --> 00:35:36,880
Come on, I'll walk you.

402
00:35:55,480 --> 00:35:57,720
Kongkwan's really happy today.

403
00:35:57,800 --> 00:35:59,160
Thank you so much.

404
00:35:59,240 --> 00:36:01,160
I'm the one who should thank you.

405
00:36:01,760 --> 00:36:04,000
It's been a while
since I had a home-cooked meal.

406
00:36:04,640 --> 00:36:07,600
Your mom and Kongkwan are so sweet too.

407
00:36:08,560 --> 00:36:10,760
Your family really feels like a home.

408
00:36:11,600 --> 00:36:12,800
Of course.

409
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:25,800
Once I'm done handling things,

410
00:36:27,600 --> 00:36:30,480
I'll take you to meet my family too.

411
00:36:36,520 --> 00:36:37,920
And

412
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:41,600
why do I need to meet them?

413
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:45,160
I just want to take my girlfriend
to meet my family.

414
00:37:35,400 --> 00:37:36,960
Would you mind toasting with me?

415
00:37:39,040 --> 00:37:40,200
How annoying.

416
00:37:42,920 --> 00:37:45,120
It's just a toast. Don't be so stuck-up.

417
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:54,600
- You want to say cheers that bad?
- Yes.

418
00:38:01,120 --> 00:38:02,280
You bitch!

419
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:06,720
- Hey!
- Let go of me! Let go!

420
00:38:06,800 --> 00:38:07,920
What's going on here?

421
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:11,440
It's you!

422
00:38:16,640 --> 00:38:17,960
Let's get out of here.

423
00:38:18,040 --> 00:38:20,160
It's dangerous. Let's go.

424
00:38:20,240 --> 00:38:21,480
Trying to run?

425
00:38:23,480 --> 00:38:27,400
If you get any closer,
prepare to spend nights in jail.

426
00:38:28,720 --> 00:38:30,160
- Give me that!
- Stop!

427
00:38:31,680 --> 00:38:32,520
‪Let's go.

428
00:38:35,920 --> 00:38:36,960
Careful.

429
00:38:39,320 --> 00:38:41,160
- Where are you going?!
- That way!

430
00:38:41,680 --> 00:38:44,600
Stop running! Stop!

431
00:38:46,360 --> 00:38:47,600
Where are you going?

432
00:38:54,320 --> 00:38:55,640
Don't be afraid of them.

433
00:39:00,200 --> 00:39:01,040
What's going on here?

434
00:39:02,560 --> 00:39:04,120
These two were harassing this woman.

435
00:39:04,720 --> 00:39:07,360
- It's you two again? When will you learn?
- Let go!

436
00:39:07,440 --> 00:39:08,800
- Come on!
- Let go!

437
00:39:13,960 --> 00:39:15,280
Are you okay?

438
00:39:16,200 --> 00:39:17,680
I'm okay.

439
00:39:40,160 --> 00:39:43,880
Can't we ever meet in a normal situation?

440
00:39:48,240 --> 00:39:49,680
My name is Bella.

441
00:39:49,760 --> 00:39:51,120
You can call me Bell.

442
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:54,560
I'm Anapat.

443
00:40:13,520 --> 00:40:16,760
Hey, it's fine. He works for me.

444
00:40:17,440 --> 00:40:19,480
Miss, you should've let me
come inside with you.

445
00:40:19,560 --> 00:40:20,520
Just now,

446
00:40:20,600 --> 00:40:22,920
if something happened to you,
your father would've killed me.

447
00:40:23,840 --> 00:40:25,040
I'm not a prisoner.

448
00:40:25,800 --> 00:40:28,200
I don't need someone
to watch me all the time.

449
00:40:29,000 --> 00:40:30,800
And don't tell Dad.

450
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:32,360
I don't want to bother explaining.

451
00:40:33,440 --> 00:40:34,280
Understood.

452
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:57,880
I hope we can meet in a normal situation
someday, Mr. Anapat.

453
00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:01,280
Yes.

454
00:41:27,080 --> 00:41:29,000
Everyone!

455
00:41:31,120 --> 00:41:33,400
- Wait.
- Don't you dare!

456
00:41:35,280 --> 00:41:37,040
- Throw me that ball.
- No!

457
00:41:41,040 --> 00:41:42,480
Thank you, Mr. Thee,

458
00:41:43,160 --> 00:41:45,640
for bringing Mom and Kongkwan along.

459
00:41:45,720 --> 00:41:48,320
It's been a while since our family
got to travel out of town.

460
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:51,640
It's nothing. You don't have to thank me.

461
00:41:56,080 --> 00:41:58,680
- Hello!
- Hello, Mr. Thee!

462
00:41:59,360 --> 00:42:01,320
What's up? Are you tired
from working so hard?

463
00:42:06,480 --> 00:42:10,960
Mook, we'll be checking out
the ballrooms and the other areas now

464
00:42:11,040 --> 00:42:12,200
for our presentation.

465
00:42:13,560 --> 00:42:17,520
Okay. Oh, don't forget to take pictures,
so we can send them to the event team.

466
00:42:17,600 --> 00:42:19,000
Sure.

467
00:42:22,880 --> 00:42:25,400
What's wrong, May? Do you need to pee?

468
00:42:27,960 --> 00:42:31,240
Mr. Thee, we'd like to thank you

469
00:42:31,320 --> 00:42:33,360
for inviting us on this vacation.

470
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:39,040
Mr. Thee invited you here to work.

471
00:42:39,120 --> 00:42:41,360
- It's not a vacation!
- Stop interrupting me!

472
00:42:44,200 --> 00:42:45,960
Thank you.

473
00:42:46,040 --> 00:42:50,360
You're welcome. Think of it as working
out of the office and also a vacation.

474
00:42:54,320 --> 00:42:55,440
Okay.

475
00:42:56,800 --> 00:42:59,240
In that case, let's get to work.

476
00:42:59,320 --> 00:43:00,560
- Yeah, go.
- Please excuse us.

477
00:43:00,640 --> 00:43:03,400
- Let's get to work.
- Don't forget to take pictures!

478
00:43:03,480 --> 00:43:06,480
- Come on!
- I know!

479
00:43:10,840 --> 00:43:12,640
Thee, come play with me!

480
00:43:14,520 --> 00:43:16,400
- I've got to go.
- Okay.

481
00:43:17,080 --> 00:43:18,880
Inviting him to get sand all over, huh?

482
00:43:19,920 --> 00:43:21,760
Don't do that. It'll get in your eyes.

483
00:43:21,840 --> 00:43:22,880
I'm coming!

484
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:27,400
Careful, you'll get sand on you.

485
00:43:27,480 --> 00:43:28,920
That's alright.

486
00:43:30,400 --> 00:43:32,240
- Here.
- What's this game?

487
00:43:32,800 --> 00:43:35,960
What's this game? Go on, tell Mr. Thee.

488
00:43:38,680 --> 00:43:42,160
Let's see, between you and Thee,
who will do better?

489
00:44:03,440 --> 00:44:04,440
Oh,

490
00:44:06,040 --> 00:44:07,360
off to work already?

491
00:44:09,040 --> 00:44:10,120
Yes.

492
00:44:10,800 --> 00:44:14,520
If I take any more days off,
I'm sure they'll fire me.

493
00:44:19,840 --> 00:44:24,120
Have you made your peace about Khim?

494
00:44:32,280 --> 00:44:33,960
I really didn't mean it.

495
00:44:35,680 --> 00:44:39,680
And also, I wasn't the one
who made a move first.

496
00:44:41,640 --> 00:44:43,280
You believe me, right?

497
00:44:51,840 --> 00:44:54,680
With bad friends,
I just have to cut them off.

498
00:44:55,480 --> 00:44:58,480
I don't have time for that nonsense, Top.

499
00:45:01,320 --> 00:45:02,520
That's more like it.

500
00:45:03,600 --> 00:45:06,400
I like it when you're this easy
to deal with.

501
00:45:16,520 --> 00:45:18,400
I'm meeting up with my friends tonight.

502
00:45:19,080 --> 00:45:20,800
I might not come home.

503
00:45:20,880 --> 00:45:22,280
Just go to bed without me.

504
00:45:25,320 --> 00:45:28,200
You can do whatever
and go wherever you want.

505
00:45:29,400 --> 00:45:32,040
It's good that we both
stay in our own lane.

506
00:45:33,720 --> 00:45:35,200
I'm off to work now.

507
00:46:48,400 --> 00:46:51,080
LET'S LEARN ABOUT IPO

508
00:47:12,760 --> 00:47:14,400
My unit isn't so big.

509
00:47:15,040 --> 00:47:16,280
‪You're okay with it?

510
00:47:17,000 --> 00:47:18,960
‪Of course. No problem at all.

511
00:47:19,760 --> 00:47:21,600
Let me give you a tour.

512
00:47:21,680 --> 00:47:22,920
This is the kitchen.

513
00:47:23,440 --> 00:47:25,680
- Back there is the laundry room.
- Okay.

514
00:47:26,240 --> 00:47:28,280
And here…

515
00:47:30,560 --> 00:47:32,680
Here's the restroom.

516
00:47:35,880 --> 00:47:39,720
This is the storage room.

517
00:47:44,160 --> 00:47:45,360
And then this

518
00:47:46,560 --> 00:47:48,200
is our bedroom.

519
00:47:48,720 --> 00:47:50,080
Isn't it lovely?

520
00:47:50,720 --> 00:47:52,040
It is.

521
00:47:52,120 --> 00:47:54,560
It's got an en-suite bathroom
and a walk-in closet.

522
00:47:57,480 --> 00:47:59,480
What about this room, Top?

523
00:48:01,720 --> 00:48:03,920
It's my office.

524
00:48:04,000 --> 00:48:06,160
It's so messy, though.

525
00:48:07,120 --> 00:48:09,360
Please don't tidy up in there,

526
00:48:09,440 --> 00:48:12,480
- or I'll lose track of my stuff.
- Okay.

527
00:48:13,680 --> 00:48:15,400
Are you fine with living here?

528
00:48:15,480 --> 00:48:16,920
Yes.

529
00:48:49,440 --> 00:48:52,200
I left something at my condo.

530
00:48:52,280 --> 00:48:54,000
I'll meet you in a bit. Okay.

531
00:50:13,600 --> 00:50:15,360
How'd it go with the police?

532
00:50:15,440 --> 00:50:18,000
<i>I'm okay. Don't worry about me, Mook.</i>

533
00:50:18,080 --> 00:50:20,240
I've got some evidence now,

534
00:50:20,320 --> 00:50:22,720
but we'll have to plan really well.

535
00:50:22,800 --> 00:50:25,360
<i>Top's a cunning guy.</i>

536
00:50:25,440 --> 00:50:27,560
<i>We'll need to catch him red-handed.</i>

537
00:50:28,200 --> 00:50:31,320
Okay. Well, if I can help
in any way, just let me know.

538
00:50:32,040 --> 00:50:33,280
Be careful, Ploy.

539
00:50:34,440 --> 00:50:37,040
I won't let him hurt me anymore, Mook.

540
00:50:37,120 --> 00:50:39,080
<i>Talk to you later.</i>

541
00:50:39,160 --> 00:50:40,120
Okay.

542
00:50:53,120 --> 00:50:55,160
Is something wrong?
You seemed pretty serious.

543
00:50:56,760 --> 00:50:58,800
My friend called asking for some advice.

544
00:51:00,000 --> 00:51:00,840
Is it Ms. Khim?

545
00:51:01,640 --> 00:51:04,120
It's Ploy, another best friend of mine.

546
00:51:04,200 --> 00:51:05,800
I'll introduce you later.

547
00:51:08,880 --> 00:51:10,080
Where's Kongkwan and my mom?

548
00:51:10,720 --> 00:51:13,760
Kongkwan got tired, so your mom
took her back to their room to rest.

549
00:51:15,080 --> 00:51:17,480
Do you want to eat? I'll order something.

550
00:51:17,560 --> 00:51:18,640
Hello, Mr. Thee.

551
00:51:20,480 --> 00:51:22,480
This is Mr. Chadchai.
He's the manager here.

552
00:51:24,080 --> 00:51:25,360
This is Mook.

553
00:51:25,440 --> 00:51:26,560
She's my girlfriend.

554
00:51:27,720 --> 00:51:28,680
Hey.

555
00:51:30,560 --> 00:51:34,240
Hello. I'm Mook. I'm Mr. Thee's assistant.

556
00:51:34,320 --> 00:51:35,640
Hello, Ms. Mook.

557
00:51:36,520 --> 00:51:39,080
I've already taken care
of that thing we talked about.

558
00:51:41,360 --> 00:51:42,840
Let's talk in the meeting room.

559
00:51:42,920 --> 00:51:44,280
Sure.

560
00:51:44,360 --> 00:51:45,600
If you'll excuse me.

561
00:51:46,240 --> 00:51:47,080
Sure.

562
00:52:25,360 --> 00:52:27,960
{\an8}HOUSE NO. 12/3 - TWO METERS - ONE MINUTE

563
00:52:31,160 --> 00:52:33,320
<i>What do you need Preaw's address for?</i>

564
00:52:34,880 --> 00:52:36,560
My friend's opening a coffee shop.

565
00:52:36,640 --> 00:52:38,480
She's looking for someone to help her,

566
00:52:38,560 --> 00:52:41,120
so I wanted to ask Preaw if she'd be down.

567
00:52:41,720 --> 00:52:44,680
Why not call and ask her? It's easier.

568
00:52:46,480 --> 00:52:48,000
She must've changed her phone number.

569
00:52:48,080 --> 00:52:49,160
I can't get a hold of her.

570
00:52:49,240 --> 00:52:51,400
I went to her house,
but she wasn't there either.

571
00:52:51,480 --> 00:52:54,040
She must've moved back
out of town to her other house.

572
00:52:54,120 --> 00:52:56,880
That's why I came to ask you if you know

573
00:52:56,960 --> 00:52:59,120
the address of her house
that's in another province.

574
00:53:00,720 --> 00:53:02,080
I think I may have it

575
00:53:02,160 --> 00:53:06,120
because Preaw's asked me
to mail something there before.

576
00:53:06,200 --> 00:53:09,240
Let me find it first,
then I'll send it right over.

577
00:53:10,480 --> 00:53:12,480
Okay. Thanks.

578
00:53:30,360 --> 00:53:33,280
Khim? How'd you get here?

579
00:53:39,920 --> 00:53:43,000
Take this money
and take your son to the doctor.

580
00:53:43,080 --> 00:53:44,680
Don't worry about your work.

581
00:53:44,760 --> 00:53:46,760
Take care of him until he gets better.

582
00:53:47,560 --> 00:53:49,160
Thank you so much.

583
00:53:49,240 --> 00:53:52,240
If it weren't for you, I don't think
my son would make it, Mrs. Narin.

584
00:53:52,840 --> 00:53:54,280
Thank you.

585
00:54:00,360 --> 00:54:01,320
Oh, Ms. Mook!

586
00:54:01,400 --> 00:54:03,640
- Hello, Mrs. Narin.
- Hello.

587
00:54:04,160 --> 00:54:06,520
Is that housekeeper okay?

588
00:54:07,200 --> 00:54:09,000
Her son's sick,

589
00:54:09,080 --> 00:54:11,200
so I told her to take some time off
to look after him.

590
00:54:12,400 --> 00:54:14,040
That's so kind of you.

591
00:54:14,120 --> 00:54:15,760
You sure take good care of your staff.

592
00:54:16,560 --> 00:54:18,520
My staff are like my family.

593
00:54:18,600 --> 00:54:21,840
If there's something
I can do to help, I'll gladly try my best.

594
00:54:22,800 --> 00:54:24,360
Are you here on vacation?

595
00:54:24,440 --> 00:54:25,640
Did you book a room yet?

596
00:54:25,720 --> 00:54:28,320
Oh, I already checked in,

597
00:54:28,400 --> 00:54:29,920
but I'm not exactly on vacation.

598
00:54:30,000 --> 00:54:32,840
I'm here with Mr. Thee
to scout the venue for an event.

599
00:54:33,800 --> 00:54:35,440
So Mr. Thee's here too?

600
00:54:36,040 --> 00:54:40,360
Yes, he said he'd use this place
as the venue for our campaign.

601
00:54:40,440 --> 00:54:42,320
He said it's one of his group's hotels.

602
00:54:45,800 --> 00:54:49,200
Did he not notify you in advance?

603
00:54:52,960 --> 00:54:54,960
- I'm really sorry.
- Oh!

604
00:54:55,040 --> 00:54:58,520
I thought he already notified you,
so I had my staff scout the hotel.

605
00:54:59,120 --> 00:55:00,480
No worries at all.

606
00:55:00,560 --> 00:55:03,720
Mr. Thee will become
the hotel's partner anyway.

607
00:55:04,480 --> 00:55:05,600
How about this?

608
00:55:05,680 --> 00:55:09,720
Let me give you a tour of my hotel,
so we can talk while we walk.

609
00:55:10,320 --> 00:55:12,000
Sounds good! Thank you so much.

610
00:55:12,080 --> 00:55:14,720
- Let's go. This way.
- I really appreciate it.

611
00:55:14,800 --> 00:55:16,200
How long are you staying with us?

612
00:55:16,280 --> 00:55:20,000
Uh, I'm not sure yet, but…

613
00:55:23,240 --> 00:55:24,760
This is the small ballroom.

614
00:55:24,840 --> 00:55:27,200
It seats up to 50 people.

615
00:55:27,280 --> 00:55:30,520
The main ballroom
for activities is just upstairs.

616
00:55:30,600 --> 00:55:31,440
I see.

617
00:55:32,600 --> 00:55:33,960
Let's take a look, shall we?

618
00:55:34,640 --> 00:55:36,760
Oh, Mrs. Narin.
It's good that you're here.

619
00:55:40,160 --> 00:55:43,160
Mr. Thee's here to scout the venue
for The One's new campaign.

620
00:55:43,240 --> 00:55:45,520
I was just about to let you know.

621
00:55:45,600 --> 00:55:47,920
Hello, Mr. Thee. Welcome.

622
00:55:54,600 --> 00:55:57,040
I've gone over the contract with Mr. Thee.

623
00:55:57,120 --> 00:55:59,240
Did you find any issues with it?

624
00:56:00,800 --> 00:56:04,200
If everything looks good,
we can sign it soon.

625
00:56:04,920 --> 00:56:06,200
Everything looks good.

626
00:56:06,280 --> 00:56:07,640
Let's set a date for the signing.

627
00:56:13,240 --> 00:56:15,880
Let's go eat. I'm hungry.

628
00:56:15,960 --> 00:56:17,880
Let's not keep
your mom and Kongkwan waiting.

629
00:56:19,160 --> 00:56:21,120
Then, if you'll excuse me.

630
00:56:21,200 --> 00:56:23,480
Thank you for the tour, Mrs. Narin.

631
00:56:25,400 --> 00:56:27,640
I should go read the contract again.

632
00:56:28,720 --> 00:56:29,800
Okay.

633
00:56:38,960 --> 00:56:41,360
Why are you so cold towards Mrs. Narin?

634
00:56:44,040 --> 00:56:46,520
Is there a problem between you two?

635
00:56:49,560 --> 00:56:51,360
Not really.

636
00:56:52,800 --> 00:56:54,560
It's just my work style.

637
00:56:55,680 --> 00:56:57,200
I need a clear boundary.

638
00:57:00,600 --> 00:57:03,160
Why'd you want to invest in this place?

639
00:57:03,920 --> 00:57:05,720
After all, in this economy,

640
00:57:06,320 --> 00:57:08,600
a hotel won't be able to make much profit.

641
00:57:12,960 --> 00:57:16,280
Because what I'll get
is more than just a profit.

642
00:57:18,560 --> 00:57:21,080
I'll get to do
what I've been longing to do.

643
00:57:23,880 --> 00:57:27,440
{\an8}I'm not ready to face
the same problems again.

644
00:57:31,240 --> 00:57:34,760
{\an8}You should go back to be
with your fiancée and your mom.

645
00:57:39,600 --> 00:57:40,760
{\an8}Mook…

646
00:57:43,600 --> 00:57:45,000
{\an8}- Boss!
- Boss!

647
00:57:46,640 --> 00:57:49,840
{\an8}You told me to compete with you, remember?

648
00:57:51,960 --> 00:57:55,360
{\an8}…that Bell is the fiancée of Thee,

649
00:57:55,440 --> 00:57:57,000
{\an8}an executive at TJ Group.

650
00:57:57,720 --> 00:58:02,120
{\an8}We also have some great news
to share with you very soon.

651
00:58:56,120 --> 00:58:58,320
{\an8}Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

